name: Rumah Makan Anda Pupuan
address: Jl. Gajah Mada No.64, Pupuan, Kec. Pupuan, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82163, Indonesia
review 1:
A legendary place is always a tricky one. You either loved it so much, or you regret it completely.

But this one is kinda in the middle. The food is not that good, it's either a little bit too salty or too bland for my taste buds.

Not sure if I'll come back.
review 2:
This place has a long history.
It is very popular among the locals. I have been dining here since I was a child. My Dad usually took me to this place when we went to De pasar or Tabanan.

Today, I often take my kids to this place as well.

It is open from about 6 a.m until about 3 or 4 p.m. Its speciality is Balinese food. You can enjoy you meal here but sometimes you need to wait for a table.

If you are in a hurry, you can have your food wrapped.

Price? Just moderate.
review 3: Just back to memorize pupuan local food, but today the taste is too salty, local tourist 23k per portion, just get soup, bunch of rice, crispy chicken skin, 1 pcs satay, 2 kinds meat, not get dry meat (don't know why) it is bit upset, out of expectation. not recommended for now. Need an approvement!
review 4: The local delicacy to get when visiting pupuan, we recommend getting the mixed rice with the soup to enjoy your lunch after visiting the sleeping buddha
